  abstract = {This work is intended to foster a {\textquotedblleft}quantum leap{\textquotedblright} in the reflection on learning in smart cities/territories. We try to move from a vision according to which education is identified with {\textquotedblleft}infrastructures and services{\textquotedblright} needed to sustain the smart city {\textquotedblleft}organism{\textquotedblright} (due also to the social capital that it may produce) toward a {\textquotedblleft}new{\textquotedblright} vision that recovers the founding role of the educative processes, through which the relationships between persons and inhabited territories are continuously reshaped. According to that we present: a) a
